29/02/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Albanian Defence Minister Pandeli Majko will arrive on Monday (1 March) on a two-day official visit to Bulgaria at the invitation of his Bulgarian counterpart, Nikolai Svinarov. 
The objective of the visit is to discuss the NATO and EU integration process and ways of enhancing bilateral co-operation.
Majko traveled Sunday to Macedonia, where he expressed condolences for the death of Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski. 
He will also hold a meeting with his Macedonian counterpart, Vlado Buckovski. 
(Macedonian Radio - 29/02/04; BTA - 27/02/04)
